==English==
===Etymology===
Coined erroneously in the early 20th century in confusion with the neighbouring Hattites (Hattic) whose language was recorded in discovered texts as ''hasili''. It is now know that the Hittites called themselves ''nesili'' "pertaining to the city of Nesa",
hence the less popular alternative name [[Nesite]] or [[Neshite]].

===Noun===
'''Hittite'''

#The Hittite people or language.

===Adjective===
'''Hittite'''

#Of or relating to the Hittite people.
#Of or relating to the Hittite language which is derived from [[Proto-Indo-European]].
#Of or relating to the Hittite Kingdom, located in central Anatolia (modern Turkey), that flourished from about 1800 to 1400 BCE.